==English==

===Etymology===
The ''lo'' from the expression likely originated from the shortening of the word ''loke'', commonly seen in [[Middle English]] texts. Its presence in literature can be traced as far back as the [[1800s]].  It is possible to reach the conclusion that said expression is a redundancy, as it literally means "look and look".

===Interjection===
'''[[lo]] [[and]] [[behold]]'''
# [[suddenly]]

